<title>Metro-North Bronx Shuttle Bus Stops, New York NY, May 2019</title>
<creator>Frank Donnelly</creator>
<creator>Anastasia Clark</creator>
<subject>structure</subject>
<subject>transportation</subject>
<description>This point layer represents shuttle bus stops in the northwest Bronx that provide connecting service to the Metro-North railroad, a commuter rail system that connects southwestern Connecticut and the Hudson Valley in New York State to New York City. Each point represents a bus stop for the Hudson Rail Link, a shuttle service that connects residents in the northwest Bronx to the Spuyten Duyvil and Riverdale stations on the Metro-North's Hudson Line. The unique ID for the features is stop_id, a field created by the MTA. This layer was created by the GIS Lab at Baruch College CUNY as part of the NYC Mass Transit Spatial Layer series, to provide access to mass transit features for basic geographic analysis and map making. The data was generated from the MTA's static data developer feeds. It was transformed and generalized from a GTFS format into readily usable GIS features using a series of python scripts.</description>
